            . I have known him three years; I never heard any harm of him. He is an industrious man.</p>
               <p>Mr. Jones. He said, before Sir 
               <persName id="t17710410-25-person242">
                  John
                   Fielding
               <interp inst="t17710410-25-person242" type="surname" value="Fielding"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710410-25-person242" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710410-25-person242" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , that he had hit his knee against a boat, and that made him limp.</p>
               <p>Q. to Cook. Did you observe him lame?</p>
               <p>Cook. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17710410-25-person243">
                  John
                   Norris
               <interp inst="t17710410-25-person243" type="surname" value="Norris"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710410-25-person243" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17710410-25-person243" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known him sixteen years: he was a shipmate of mine, the last war, eight years. He has a good character.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17710410-25-person244">
                  Rachael
                   Richardson
               <interp inst="t17710410-25-person244" type="surname" value="Richardson"></interp>
